cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI

This paper is about machine learning theory and specifically addresses the problem of recovering the lowest layer in a deep neural network. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with neural networks, which suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of Gaussian input distributions, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper's focus on modeling networks as well-behaved polynomials could suggest cs.CV (Computer Vision) as a possible sub-category.
